All sport in Italy has been suspended until at least 3 April because of coronavirus; the country's Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte, BBCSport has reported. The report says, Serie A will be affected but not Italian clubs or national teams participating in international competitions including UEFA Champions League. Serie A - Italy's top flight - had already said all games would be played behind closed doors until 3 April. Conte extended a series of strict quarantine measures, including a ban on public gatherings, to all of Italy. Earlier, Italy's Olympic committee (CONI) recommended the move to suspend all sport at all levels after hosting a special meeting of sporting federations on Monday. Italy has been the European country worst hit by coronavirus so far, with over 9,000 confirmed cases and more than 450 deaths. SOURCE: BBCSPORTS